OL,3,CCovid Inquiry: Matt Hancock says PPE
OL,4,Cwas within hours from running out
OL,6,FLead counsel to the inquiry,
OL,7,FJacqueline Carey KC, asked Mr Hancock:
OL,8,F"Do you accept that entering the
OL,9,Fcoronavirus pandemic as we did,
OL,10,Fwithout a single gown, severely
OL,11,Fhampered the ability to provide safe
OL,12,Fand appropriate PPE for healthcare
OL,13,Fworkers?"
OL,15,FMr Hancock replied: "The stockpile
OL,16,Fthat we had was not as good as it
OL,17,Fneeds to be in the future, absolutely."
OL,19,FAsked if England ever ran out of PPE,
OL,20,Fhe said: "As a whole? No, but
OL,21,Findividual locations did.
